<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96657739115643></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96657739115643><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=96657739115643>RE: lvl 15</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=96657739115643#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:43 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Levels 15 to 24 are all awful =)&nbsp;&nbsp;At 14 you are happy for new spells, but the novelty wears off.  Level 19 spells, well they stink.  A couple look promising, but overall it is a huge disappointment.  Once you hit 24, life gets SO much better.  I shelved my guy at 17, then gave him another chance almost 6 months later.  Once I hit 24, my jaw dropped (250 poison DoT, 150 DD, regen, cannabilize) and have not looked back.  Give it time, and be patient.  Shaman are horrible below 24.  Well, horrible is a strong word.  But onced you hit 24, you will feel like you are playing an entirely different character.<br>Get a group, make some friends, and at least the time will go quicker.  Beyond that *shrug* I have no secrets for those levels, except maybe the Sirens in OOT.  Pretty good xp til 17, rarely camped =)<br>Gorthin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
